title: MacBookPro Retina A1502. fluctuate at 200mAmp
message: I got a liquid damage 820-4924-A. It was corroded near U7600 and U8330. And initially was stucked at 120mAmp. After cleaning replacing R8185, It stopped taking 120mAmp but now when power on takes 180-220mAmp for 1 second only then goes to zero. i also check at same time it produces S0 rails and Powergood signals just for 1 Sec.  I didn't found any other liquid damage or short circuit. check SPI Rom and related signal all are present and normal. when it is in off state, only have S5 rails. PM_PCH_PWORK goes off.  I looked for some other stuffs but i have admit i don't know where to look?

title: MacBookPro Retina A1502. fluctuate at 200mAmp
message:
For liquid spilled boards, is recommended to reball SMC.
CPU_VCSST_PWRGD and PM_PCH_SYS_PWROK pulsing?
Also check for pulse at PLT_RESET_L.

Try to start in SMC bypass mode too.
